-- New York City June Average Taxi Medallion Sales Price
-- B y   A i n h o a   G o y e n e c h e
-- 2012-06-29T20:53:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-29/new-york-city-june-average-taxi-medallion-sales-price-table-.html
The cost of an individual taxi cab medallion was
unchanged in June, according to the  New York  City Taxi and Limousine Commission.  The medallion, the aluminum plate found on the hood of all cabs in
 New York City , gives the owner the right to operate a taxi. In June, the
average price was unchanged at $704,000 from $704,000 a month earlier.
This month 17 individual medallions were transferred; 84 have been transferred
in 2012.             To contact the reporter on this story:
